tags: A different kind of story for
Life and times of my cardboard cutouts
summary: So, my partner and I moved to a new house last week, and we hired movers because we both have waaaaay too much stuff. And...
body:
So, my partner and I moved to a new house last week, and we hired movers because we both have waaaaay too much stuff. And yesterday we went to the old apartment to clean up. This is the scene that greeted us when we opened the door to our old entry closet. The movers forgot a couple of things!

My partner was like, “What’s going on here?” and I quipped, “Looks like some Tencest in the closet.”

About an hour later I notice that my partner posted the photo on her Facebook page. And a friend of hers had commented, “Are those cardboard cutouts?” Which I, being a bit sensitive about my obsession with David Tennant, took to be snark. So, I might have replied, “No! The actual Tenth Doctor and his metacrisis self stopped by tonight to say hello, and helped us clear out the apartment. It’s a funny story - they took all of my hair products, said something about Dårlig Ulv-Stranden, and vanished in the TARDIS. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯”

Late last night I mentioned this to my partner, and she gave me a look, and told me the guy who had asked wasn’t being a smart arse, he’s an old man with no kids who was genuinely not sure what they were. And probably has no idea what Doctor Who is, never mind Tentoo. So I uh … may have slightly overreacted. Anyway, I apologized, so as long as nobody on her Facebook page mentions Tencest, I think I might get through this little interlude ok.
